    "Under suitable assumptions, for each random initialization ω ∈ Ω on the non-trainable parameters (B (t)) T +1 t=1, define the LoRA function space F equipped with the metric induced by the uniform norm ∥ • ∥ ∞:F def.",
    "= F(ω, M) = {LoRA(ω, (A (t)) T +1 t=1) ∈ C([0, 1] d, R D): |A (t) ij | ≤ M, ∀t, i, j}.Then, for every ϵ, ε > 0 the ε-covering number N (ε, F) of F satisfiesP N (ε, F) ≤ (2R + 2R 0) cT +1 /ε q ≥ P(B ϵ) ≥ 1 -ϵ(12)where c = c 2, R = M ν 2r log(2W/ϵ) and R 0 = ∥θ pre ∥ ∞ as in Lemma 9.Step 3 -Generalization Bounds Conditioned on Covering Number Bounds We control the randomized generalization gap G conditioned on the event B ϵ, as defined in (16).",
    "Upon conditioning on the right realizations, which occurs with high probability, our covering number bounds give us access to Dudley's integral estimate; see e.g.",
    "[van der Vaart and Wellner, 1996, Corollary 2.2.8].",
    "Lemma 3 (Conditional Generalization Bounds for \"Derandomized\" LoRAs)."
  ],
